# GVV Website Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Deploy the institutional website for `gv.ventures` for the first client demo. The project leverages **Next.js (SSG)** for extreme performance and security, **Sanity** for headless CMS, and **HubSpot** for CRM. 
The design system is cloned from Vistra.com, while the sitemap hierarchy is cloned from TaurusWealth.com and populated with the provided Website Copy document.

## Proposed Changes

### Setup & Infrastructure
- Initialize Next.js app in the working directory using `npx create-next-app@latest .`
- Configure global CSS to match Vistra's design tokens (Primary Navy: `#0012B7`, Fonts: `Outfit` / `Montserrat`).

### Core Components
#### [NEW] `components/Navbar.tsx`
- Transparent-to-Solid sticky navigation matching the Vistra layout.

#### [NEW] `components/Footer.tsx`
- Deep navy institutional 3-column footer.

#### [NEW] `components/Hero.tsx`
- Large container with deep rounded bottom-right corners (40px-60px radius) and large H1 overlay.

#### [NEW] `components/Button.tsx`
- Fully rounded 50px pill button components.

#### [NEW] `components/Card.tsx`
- Clean white/grey cards with 20px rounded corners for services and insight feeds.

### Site Pages
#### [NEW] `app/page.tsx` - Home Page
#### [NEW] `app/about-us/page.tsx` - About Us
#### [NEW] `app/our-capabilities/page.tsx` - Our Capabilities (with sticky tab-nav)
#### [NEW] `app/insights/page.tsx` - Insights Hub
#### [NEW] `app/platform/page.tsx` - Platform
#### [NEW] `app/team/page.tsx` - Team
#### [NEW] `app/careers/page.tsx` - Careers
#### [NEW] `app/privacy-policy/page.tsx` - Legal: Privacy Policy
#### [NEW] `app/disclaimer/page.tsx` - Legal: Disclaimer

### Integrations
- **CMS (Sanity):** Initialize Sanity Studio for the "Insights" data schema. Create `lib/sanity.ts` to fetch Insights for the home page and insights listing page.
- **CRM (HubSpot):** Create `components/ContactForm.tsx` to handle the standard "Contact Us" interactions and submit data securely using the HubSpot Forms API.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Build Tests
- Command: `npm run build`
- Ensure the SSG build succeeds without any missing static dependencies or typing errors.

### Visual Validation
- Command: `npm run dev`
- Use the autonomous browser subagent to record a walkthrough of all implemented pages (Checking responsivness, routing, and Vistra design cloning precision).

### Integration Verification
- **CMS Checklist:** Seed a dummy article in the Sanity Studio and verify it appears on the `/insights` feed.
- **CRM Checklist:** Submit a test lead through the Contact Form intercept and verify standard HTTP response success.
